<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-16T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="1050" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1050">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.20 Missions/11–1545: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-16T20:00:00-05:00">November
                                    16, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>346. Uriel 557, Nov. 15, 10 a.m. Note 922 not reed. Assuming it deals
                            with same subject as 901, Dept authorizes return of both notes in your
                            discretion but recommends matter be handled informally and orally with
                            Foreign Minister.<note n="37" xml:id="d1050fn37">The Ambassador
                                indicated in his telegram 564, November 17, 1945, 11 a.m., that the
                                notes were returned (834.20 Missions/11–1745).</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>